{
  "texts": [
    "We coined the term prompting pedagogy to capture fundamental pedagogical practices involved in generating games or other digital outputs with the help of LLMs going beyond prompt engineering as discussed above and constituting one aspect of a new pedagogy of learning with AI.",
    "While prompt engineering will be a crucial competence for harnessing the potential of AI in education (Eager & Brunton, 2023), we also want to emphasize that the ability to critically evaluate generated outputs and its facilitation by existing (domain) expertise are equally important (Dwivedi et al., 2023; Krügel et al., 2023).",
    "This critical evaluation informs the crafting of prompts leading to meaningful and constructive dialogue with LLMs.",
    "Such cumulative and continuous dialog is crucial when using LLMs in complex tasks like game-making.",
    "Moreover, using LLMs in such a reflective and critical manner enhances critical thinking and problem-based learning (Bernabei et al., 2023; Sallam, 2023; Shue et al., 2023)."
  ]
}